# 💼 Personal Portfolio Website

A fully **responsive personal portfolio website** built with **React.js**, designed to showcase my projects, skills, and professional information. Perfect for personal branding and professional use. 🚀

## ✨ Features

- 🌐 **Responsive Design**: Works perfectly on desktop, tablet, and mobile devices
- 🎨 **Modern UI**: Clean, interactive, and visually appealing interface using React components
- 🔗 **Smooth Navigation**: Sticky navbar with smooth scrolling between sections
- 🛠 **Project Showcase**: Highlight projects with images, descriptions, and live links
- 💻 **Skills & Experience**: Display technical skills, work experience, and education
- 📬 **Contact Section**: Includes social links and contact form integration
- ⚡ **Performance Optimized**: Fast loading and optimized for better user experience

## 🛠 Technologies Used

- ⚛️ **Frontend**: React.js, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- 🎨 **Styling**: CSS3, React Icons
- 🚀 **Build Tools**: Vite, npm/yarn
- 🔄 **Version Control**: Git, GitHub
- 🌍 **Deployment**: Vercel/Netlify/GitHub Pages

## 🚀 Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (v14 or later)
- npm (v6 or later) or yarn
- Git

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/portfolio-website.git
   cd portfolio-website
   ```

2. **Install dependencies**
   ```bash
   npm install
   # or
   yarn install
   ```

3. **Start development server**
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   # or
   yarn dev
   ```
   Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.

## 🛠 Project Structure

```
portfolio/
├── public/           # Static files
├── src/
│   ├── assets/       # Images, icons, etc.
│   ├── components/   # Reusable components
│   ├── data/         # Project data and content
│   ├── pages/        # Page components
│   ├── styles/       # Global styles
│   ├── App.jsx       # Main App component
│   └── main.jsx      # Entry point
├── .gitignore
├── package.json
└── README.md
```

## 🚀 Deploy on Vercel

1. **Prepare your repository**
   - Make sure all your changes are committed and pushed to your GitHub repository
   - Ensure you have a `.env` file with all required environment variables (use `.env.example` as a reference)

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   - Go to [Vercel](https://vercel.com/) and sign in with your GitHub account
   - Click on "Add New..." and select "Project"
   - Import your GitHub repository
   - Vercel will automatically detect it's a Vite + React project
   - Configure environment variables (if any) in the Vercel dashboard:
     - Go to Project Settings > Environment Variables
     - Add variables from your `.env` file
   - Click "Deploy"

3. **Set up custom domain (optional)**
   - Go to your project in Vercel
   - Click on "Settings" > "Domains"
   - Add your custom domain and follow the verification steps

## 📝 Customization

1. Update `src/data/projects.js` to add/remove projects
2. Modify `src/data/skills.js` to update your skills
3. Edit `src/data/about.js` to update your personal information
4. Customize colors and styles in `src/styles/`

